---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How builtwithjon.com collects, uses, and protects your information."
>
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="legal-updated">Last Updated: March 23, 2026</p>

    <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
    <p>
      This Privacy Policy explains how Jonathan Malkin ("I," "me," "my") collects, uses, and
      protects information when you visit builtwithjon.com (the "Site").
    </p>
    <p>The Site is a personal blog and portfolio. I aim to collect as little data as possible.</p>

    <h2>2. Information I Collect</h2>

    <h3>2.1 Information You Provide</h3>
    <p>
      <strong>Email address</strong>: If you subscribe to my newsletter, I collect your email
      address through the subscription form.
    </p>

    <h3>2.2 Information Collected Automatically</h3>
    <p>
      <strong>Analytics data</strong>: I use Cloudflare Web Analytics, which collects page views,
      referrers, browser type, and approximate location. Cloudflare Web Analytics is privacy-focused:
      it does not use cookies, does not track individual visitors across sites, and does not collect
      personal information. Data is aggregated and not tied to individual users.
    </p>

    <h2>3. How I Use Information</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Newsletter</strong>: To send you articles and updates when new content is published.
        You can unsubscribe at any time using the link in any email.</li>
      <li><strong>Analytics</strong>: To understand overall traffic patterns and improve the Site.
        I do not track individual visitors.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>I use the following services to operate the Site:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Buttondown</strong>: Newsletter management. When you subscribe, your email address
        is sent to Buttondown for delivery.
        <a href="https://buttondown.com/legal/privacy">Buttondown's Privacy Policy</a></li>
      <li><strong>Cloudflare</strong>: Website hosting (Cloudflare Pages) and analytics
        (Cloudflare Web Analytics).
        <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/">Cloudflare's Privacy Policy</a></li>
    </ul>
    <p>I do not sell, rent, or share your personal information with anyone else.</p>

    <h2>5. Cookies</h2>
    <p>The Site does not use cookies. Cloudflare Web Analytics is cookieless by design.</p>

    <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Email addresses</strong>: Retained while your newsletter subscription is active.
        Removed upon unsubscribe.</li>
      <li><strong>Analytics</strong>: Cloudflare retains aggregated analytics data per their retention
        policies. No individual visitor data is stored by me.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>7. Your Rights and Choices</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Unsubscribe</strong>: Use the unsubscribe link in any newsletter email.</li>
      <li><strong>Access or delete</strong>: Contact me to request access to or deletion of your
        email address.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      If you are a California resident (CCPA) or Texas resident (TDPSA), you have additional rights
      to know, correct, and delete personal information. I do not sell personal data.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>
      The Site is intended for a general audience. I do not knowingly collect information from
      children under 13.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      I may update this Privacy Policy by posting a revised version and updating the
      "Last Updated" date.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Jonathan Malkin<br />
      Email: <a href="mailto:jonathan@builtwithjon.com">jonathan@builtwithjon.com</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>
